      "data": {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "The testing stage evaluates the deployed system against 4 Specific Objectives (SO) through 30 distinct tests across 3 execution categories. Unlike a single end-to-end acceptance test, this protocol isolates each subsystem (biometrics, blockchain, credential lifecycle, and system-level performance) so that failures can be attributed to specific layers rather than the system as a whole."
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "Tests for SO1–SO4 are system characterization protocols: they measure and describe the system's behavior under controlled conditions. A separate inferential hypothesis test validates the core architectural claim: that credential-layer enforcement makes revocation structurally binding rather than merely a policy suggestion."
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "The three execution categories reflect the nature of each test's data source. Programmatic tests reproduce results from pre-collected datasets independently of the live cluster. Blockchain benchmarks stress the consensus layer using a hybrid Caliper and custom Axios harness under a 2³ factorial design with ascending send-rates from 25 to 1,500 TPS. Live cohort tests exercise the full deployed pipeline with 50 real participants performing 200 cross-node genuine attempts and 50 presentation attacks."
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "caption": "Execution Categories",
            "headers": [
              "Category",
              "Description"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "Programmatic Tests",
                "Run against pre-collected datasets; reproducible outputs independent of live cluster"
              ],
              [
                "Blockchain Benchmarks",
                "Hybrid Caliper + custom Axios harness; 2³ factorial design; ascending send-rates 25–1,500 TPS"
              ],
              [
                "Live Cohort Tests",
                "50 participants; 200 cross-node genuine attempts; 50 presentation attacks"
              ]
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "prose",
            "text": "The table below maps every test to its parent objective, its purpose, and the statistical metric used to evaluate it. SO1 (8 tests) covers the biometric subsystem, from backbone selection to live cohort accuracy. SO2 (8 tests) covers blockchain integrity and scalability, from gas determinism to I/O bottleneck exclusion. SO3 (6 tests) covers credential lifecycle enforcement, from smart contract guards to biometric leakage audit. SO4 (8 tests) covers system-level performance, from enrollment latency to state overhead."
          },
